<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idca68a6a5-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598" identifier="/us/usc/t43/s1654"><num value="1654">§ 1654.</num><heading> Antitrust laws</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The grant of a right-of-way, permit, lease, or other authorization pursuant to this chapter shall grant no immunity from the operation of the Federal anti-trust laws.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idca68a6a6-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598">(<ref href="/us/pl/93/153/tII/s205">Pub. L. 93–153, title II, § 205</ref>, <date date="1973-11-16">Nov. 16, 1973</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/87/588">87 Stat. 588</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
